    "Lloyd R. Bailey": "There, the Israelites were encouraged to \u201cHarass the Midianites `[nation_Midian_Gen_25]`, and\ndefeat them. . . .\u201d An account of the actualization of that dramatic\ncall now opens with, \u201cAvenge the Israelites on the Midianites `[nation_Midian_Gen_25]`.\u201d\nThree related topics are presented in the chapter (only partially\nindicated by the paragraphs in NRSV):",
    "Mitchell G. Reddish, Nijay K. Gupta": "180",
    "Andrew Bonar, Andrew E. Hill": "Ver. 18,\nVer. 18,\nver. 18), the land is not to be under-valued,\nif a man have so large and wide a heart, and gratitude\nso warm, as to devote a field to the Lord from the time\nof one Jubilee on to the next. The Lord does not over-\nlook differences in men's views and purposes: \"Thou,\nmost upright, dost weigh the path of the just\" (Isa.\n488\nENTIRE DEVOTION TO GOD  CHAP. XXVII\nxxvi. 7). The widow's mite and Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`'s ointment are\nprecious in his sight; and. so are David `[char_David_Rut_4]`'s and Solomon `[char_Solomon_Ref]`'s\nmunificent gifts.\nBut, as in a former case, gratitude might cool, after the\nmoment ("
